<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="112" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="112">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus halli" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halli">Eulonchus halli</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species that can be distinguished by the dark leg and body colouration, erect white thoracic and abdominal pile, raised bifurcate ocellar tubercle, and a curved proboscis that is shorter than the body length.
</paragraph>
